-- H. Moser Owner May Sell Watchmaker Stake, SonntagsZeitung Says
-- B y   D e r m o t   D o h e r t y
-- 2012-03-04T11:38:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-04/h-moser-owner-may-sell-watchmaker-stake-sonntagszeitung-says.html
H. Moser & Cie., a Swiss watchmaker,
is looking for a capital injection and owner Thomas Straumann
may divide up his majority stake of 70 percent in the company,
 SonntagsZeitung  reported, without saying where it got the
information.  New Chief Executive Officer Christof Zuber, may have “put
out feelers” toward International Watch Co., owned by  Cie
Financiere Richemont SA (CFR) , the newspaper reported, without
providing more details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dermot Doherty in Geneva at 
 ddoherty9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
